description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Innovation &amp; Intelligent Automation team, we are recruiting a talented team to scale and accelerate the deployment of automation in the Trust and wider health and care community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to lead an Learning and Development programme that will equip staff0 with the skills to deliver highly complex automation projects and will then become part of wider team creating world-class automation solutions across clinical and corporate areas regionally and nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of Automation Academy Lead is pivotal to our success and vision, we are looking for a driven individual, who is excited by daily challenges and thrive in a busy and ever-changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who can support learning and development of staff needed to embed Automation within the wider clinical and corporate teams to ensure its widespread transformation benefit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will be responsible for the building and delivery of series of training to upskill internal and external cohorts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, you will bring a high level of expertise, and a passion for supporting the goals and ambitions of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: James Davis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Director of Innovation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: j.n.davis@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Darren Atkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: CTO Automation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: darrenatkins@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
